revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-03 16:03:43.000000000', 'message': "nova service-delete fails on non-child (top) cell

When you try to delete the service on non-child (api) cell in
cell environment, it throws the error:
AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'count'.

In case of child cell service-delete it works, because the
self.host_api attribute of _BaseMessageMethods class points to
'nova.compute.api.HostAPI', but in case of parent cell, the
same attribute points to 'nova.compute.cells_api.HostAPI'.
This is the reason it fails when parent cell is the target cell.

It calls host_api service_delete method after reaching on
destination host (target cell), which again calls the cells_rpcapi
service_delete method, when target cell is parent cell itself.
This time cell_name attribute is None after splitting the service_id
while processing the request on target cell, that's why it was
throwing the above error.

To resolve this issue, calling destroy method of objects.Service
class in _TargetedMessageMethods class service_delete method
instead of calling host_api service_delete method.

Change-Id: I103d7a23b38c49a66e50717a52b383922e4b5254
Closes-Bug: #1361186
"}]
commit_message:
nova service-delete fails on non-child (top) cell

When you try to delete the service on non-child (api) cell in
cell environment, it throws the error:
AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'count'.

In case of child cell service-delete it works, because the
self.host_api attribute of _BaseMessageMethods class points to
'nova.compute.api.HostAPI', but in case of parent cell, the
same attribute points to 'nova.compute.cells_api.HostAPI'.
This is the reason it fails when parent cell is the target cell.

It calls host_api service_delete method after reaching on
destination host (target cell), which again calls the cells_rpcapi
service_delete method, when target cell is parent cell itself.
This time cell_name attribute is None after splitting the service_id
while processing the request on target cell, that's why it was
throwing the above error.

To resolve this issue, calling destroy method of objects.Service
class in _TargetedMessageMethods class service_delete method
instead of calling host_api service_delete method.

Change-Id: I103d7a23b38c49a66e50717a52b383922e4b5254
Closes-Bug: #1361186

As of now, the CLI is not returning command success or failure in a manner which can be consumed by scripts (eg. for errors like when an invalid stack is specified, the CLI output is something like "Stack not found: <stack-id-or-name>", which a script needs to be already aware of to interpret as failure).
@Visnu: I agree that some additional information should be provided to the user to interpret the output value (is success or failure). IMO, this should be taken up as a separate change as it affects (almost) all the CLI commands.
@steve: We can add a parameter to return the json, however, what I am confused about, is if the parameter is not provided, how should the CLI notify an invalid attribute access (and not end up returning 'null')?'}, {'account_id': 1633, 'date': '2014-10-07 04:58:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Fixed null str returned for incorrect parameter

For resources like ResourceGroup, the output parameters are not
validated during stack creation. When a stack has an output parameter
which accesses an incorrect attribute of a resource, the output-show
command returns the string 'null'.
This fix instead returns an error indicating the incorrect attribute
being accessed.

Change-Id: I51eea4738bfefb35644a384ec6d4e9176c8f2e26
Closes-bug: #1368041

This patch adds the @_retry_on_deadlock decorator
to _instance_update(), which has been observed to be
involved in some deadlock scenarios.  As it is the point
of transaction demarcation based on the presence of
get_session(), this is an appropriate point at which the
transaction can be re-attempted in the case of deadlock.

Change-Id: Id2cfdc129ea3cfc787b73f1f3e9aa286a7c0229a
Closes-bug: 1375467
'}]
commit_message:
Add @_retry_on_deadlock to _instance_update()

This patch adds the @_retry_on_deadlock decorator
to _instance_update(), which has been observed to be
involved in some deadlock scenarios.  As it is the point
of transaction demarcation based on the presence of
get_session(), this is an appropriate point at which the
transaction can be re-attempted in the case of deadlock.

Change-Id: Id2cfdc129ea3cfc787b73f1f3e9aa286a7c0229a
Closes-bug: 1375467

[{'created': '2014-10-09 11:46:54.000000000', 'message': "Removing saving raw action/workflow result under 'task.taskName'

* If we always save raw task result under in the DB it causes problems
  if we, for example, have a huge raw result but don't need it all. We
  may just want to extract somethig from it like number of list items
  etc. E.g. array containing information about 30 VMs takes 130kb space
  and doesn't even fit  MySQL default text type.

  So if we need to save the entire raw result we can easily do that
  using:

    publish:
      full_result: $

  Or using any other key.

  This patch makes accessible the same variables defined in 'publish'
  via context key 'task.taskName'

Change-Id: I81af8496156afb3db46c016019880d84c12917ba
"}, {'created': '2014-10-09 12:45:07.000000000', 'message': "Removing saving raw action/workflow result under 'task.taskName'

  may just want to extract somethig from it like number of list items

  and doesn't even fit  MySQL default text type.

commit_message:
Removing saving raw action/workflow result under 'task.taskName'

* If we always save raw task result under in the DB it causes problems
  if we, for example, have a huge raw result but don't need it all. We
  may just want to extract somethig from it like number of list items
  etc. E.g. array containing information about 30 VMs takes 130kb space
  and doesn't even fit  MySQL default text type.

  So if we need to save the entire raw result we can easily do that
  using:

    publish:
      full_result: $

  Or using any other key.

  This patch makes accessible the same variables defined in 'publish'
  via context key 'task.taskName'

Change-Id: I81af8496156afb3db46c016019880d84c12917ba

commit_message:
Add database relationship between router and ports

Add an explicit schema relationship between a router and its ports. This
change ensures referential integrity among the entities and prevents orphaned
ports.

Change-Id: I09e8a694cdff7f64a642a39b45cbd12422132806
Closes-Bug: #1378866

Adding length() YAQL function

commit_message:
Leverage openstack.common.importutils for import_class

This patch removes the import_utils method from utils and leverages
the one in novaclient.openstack.common.importutils instead.

Change-Id: I7f27e6abe0a98fb4c71458fc9e5fc38b1af06050
Closes-bug: 1365275

commit_message:
Adds instructions for deploying instances on real hardware

The following sections have been added to the install-guide:

1. Set of instructions for configuring Neutron to talk to baremetal.
   Flat networking is taken as the usecase. Instructions for using
   other types of networks will be added eventually.
2. Set of instructions for adding the required images to glance.
   Includes instructions for creating the deploy and user images
   using disk-image builder.
3. Set of instructions for creating the baremetal flavor and
   associating the deploy images to the flavor.
4. Instruction for checking that the ipmitool on the openstack setup
   is able to control baremetal's power state.

Change-Id: If45f0f32808308cf2d451a905ca7cd840c81c7d2
Partial-Bug: 1323589

commit_message:
Add install guide for users and clean up README

* Add "Using Horizon" section to the docs, which describes
  how to install and configure Horizon. It is for operators
  who install Horizon from source code.
* Clean up README.rst as much of the information is out-of-date
  and most of it is covered by the developer docs.
* Minor update of page titles.

Change-Id: I09aab0d0bc47e07c8d663e7f7b5801e456434950

commit_message:
Correct slo middleware position swift proxy-server pipeline

The recommended position for SLO middleware has changed
in Swift (see change ID I7827dd2d9dfbb3c6424773fb2891355d47e372ba).
This change updates the swift proxy-server pipeline to move SLO
middleware to the correct position.

Related-Bug: #1315133
Change-Id: If52935ec7986adec67bb190a4509c8a8c35056c9

commit_message:
Move install bin from rpm-distro to yum

rpm-distro element was trying to install bin programs into the
image but it doesn't provide any. Move that logic into the yum
element which provides the install-packages bin.

Change-Id: Id5339fc7ffbef6327fe41f50a3e39ab30b6d0320

commit_message:
Update references to auth_token middleware

There's references to the auth_token middleware in keystoncelient.
The auth_token middleware has been moved to keystonemiddleware and
the version in keystoneclient shouldn't be used anymore.

If these references aren't updated, then when options are changed in
keystonemiddleware.auth_token the heat-api will fail to start because
there's duplicate options in keystoneclient.middleware.auth_token.

Change-Id: I04573aa5ff967afe3e00329f797fcc71b779e7b3
Closes-Bug: #1379082

commit_message:
Create Nova Scheduler IO Ops Weighter

Add a new nova scheduler weighter, sort the filter
hosts according to host io ops number, aims to
booting instances on light workload hosts.

blueprint io-ops-weight
Previously-approved: juno

Change-Id: Id283446718fe8390035fbff8c3a73b28f469ecc6

commit_message:
Skip IPv6 Tests in the OpenContrail plugin

Similar to the way we are skipping tests in the OneConvergence plugin,
introduced by Kevin Benton in 9294de441e684a81f6e802ba0564083f1ad319d6.

Partial-Bug: #1378952

Change-Id: I1650b0708af73ce63e92c55bc842607bb69efe60
(cherry picked from commit 67962943969bc737a3f680a0defc2fc9df03c429)

commit_message:
Rename package murano-api to murano

Added backward compatibility logic to murano
to enable Icehouse deployment, but depends on
setting openstack_version to 2014.1.X-6.0

blueprint fuel-deploy-juno

Co-Authored-By: Dmitry Borodaenko <dborodaenko@mirantis.com>
Change-Id: I5b7f314c3e9ff8fd34c4e2a7044e282b55ee6b7c

commit_message:
Disable PUT for IPv6 subnet attributes

In Juno we are not ready for allowing the IPv6 attributes on a subnet
to be updated after the subnet is created, because:
- The implementation for supporting updates is incomplete.
- Perceived lack of usefulness, no good use cases known yet.
- Allowing updates causes more complexity in the code.
- Have not tested that radvd, dhcp, etc. behave OK after update.

Therefore, for now, we set 'allow_put' to False for the two IPv6
attributes, ipv6_ra_mode and ipv6_address_mode. This prevents the
modes from being updated via the PUT:subnets API.

Closes-bug: #1378952

Change-Id: Id6ce894d223c91421b62f82d266cfc15fa63ed0e
(cherry picked from commit 8a08a3cb47d0dd69d4aa2e8fa661d04054fe95ae)

commit_message:
Added delta version of simulate

Previously, the Runtime.simulate functionality would only return
the actual query contents that you specified.  But sometimes
the user wants to only know the difference in that query
caused by the updates that are being simulated.

This change adds a parameter to Runtime.simulate that causes
it to return the difference in the query instead of the full
contents of the query.

Change-Id: I265ea408495479803c4f9cb6be5e6002c25b8776

commit_message:
Check for epel before installing it

instack runs this script on a system where epel has already been
installed, which causes the yum command to fail.  Only installing
the epel-release rpm when it isn't already present addresses the
issue.

Change-Id: Ia179d7c7ed69ea5f785b5dcd16394c7663a145cc

commit_message:
Fix network_gateway residue when resource deletion

Should set resource_id after network_gateway creation
instead of after network_gateway connection for
OS::Neutron::NetworkGateway, to avoid the network_gateway
residue when the resource deletion.

Change-Id: I89e1aed10685c0448a15decb95b89dbd946d39c2
Closes-bug: #1368008

commit_message:
Fix the msg encode/decode error

When using Mysql-python driver, the message id is converted to
long type, which will lead to a L letter in the last. So convert
it to int type before encoding.

Change-Id: I8792548d2882bd1e2c6c7b3273504746b7150d6f

commit_message:
autodoc: allow to exclude modules from auto-generation

Some projects need to not generate and publish documentation for some of
their modules. This patch adds an option to list modules that should be
excluded from documentation auto generation.

Change-Id: I944a6ad5faa113ca26eb32b78be1bfc41e1387ef

commit_message:
Add custom get_temp_url to RackspaceSwiftClient

Rackspace Cloud Files uses a non-OpenStack account identifier in the
URL, so the Rackspace Swift client needs its own get_temp_url method.

Change-Id: Ic90c26fca0200f1fba74d50b6aa8a75f8bcd7ef6
Closes-bug: #1378979

commit_message:
GET property which name includes resource type prefix

Currently GET call to API to retrieve property details ends with
404 error when property name includes resource type prefix.
This patch extends show method to take filters as a parameter.
If 'resource_type' is included in filters then the prefix of included
resource type is removed from property name. This enables user to look
for property name starting with prefix that comes from associated
resource type.

Change-Id: I3c4d96fbc9ce15016631017bf76089c338ac3cdc
Closes-Bug: #1367564
DocImpact
Co-Authored-By: Bartosz Fic <bartosz.fic@intel.com>
Co-Authored-By: Pawel Koniszewski <pawel.koniszewski@intel.com>

commit_message:
Remove utils.drop_unique_constraint()

This function is currently otherwise unused and does not
work correctly on SQLite, not only dropping the
target unique constraint but instead dropping all unique
constraints from the target table prior to SQLAlchemy
version 1.0 (unreleased).   The tests miss that it isn't
working as well unless SQLAlchemy 1.0 is used, in which
case they fail.

Change-Id: Icaff621fba4df289247e96b87c439c62e91543d6
Closes-bug: #1377646

commit_message:
Fix for "No existing metadata" in Horizon metadata selector.

In path 'Admin' -> 'Image' -> 'Update Metadata'

If all metadata items are added to "Existing metadata",
"No existing metadata" will be shown in "Available Metadata" menu.

This patch replace "No existing metadata" string to "No available
metadata", to make situation clear.

Change-Id: Ie04ca6c444e149860ccb6fc059fad3d770c6631f
Closes-Bug: 1369248

commit_message:
Switch to a custom NotImplementedError derivative

When a feature or method is not implemented it's useful
to throw our own derivative of a NotImplementedError error
so that we can distingush these types of errors vs actual
usage of NotImplementedError which could be thrown from
driver or user code.

Change-Id: I8d5dfb56a254f315c5509dc600a078cfef2dde0b

commit_message:
Get Alarm updating to work properly. Previously, the state would
not change back to the real state

Get Alarm Deletion to work properly. Previously, it would not clean
up the Alarms or Sub Alarms

Get the Alarm Definition Deletion Event to work correctly. Previously
it wasn't handled

Get the Alarm Definition Updated Event to work correctly, at least
for name, description and severity

Finish implementing some TODOs in AlarmCreationBolt and add tests

Fixed some code that could handle Alarm Definition Updates in
the MetricAggregationBolt but the right calls aren't made in
the rest of the code, yet

Removed some unused or duplicated test java files

Turn the tests back on as they now run

Change-Id: Idb6c92d35e2273601411ca9c0f7d7ba45c61ad55

commit_message:
Support action API requests

In some cases, the application needs to expose APIs that do not map to
the standard HTTP methods.  We support these requests using POST with
a mandatory 'action' query parameter that maps to the associated call in
the associated resource model.

Change-Id: I43bfaa954a85fa434beb1c5cf7b1ae18036f9ede

commit_message:
Single quote iniset argument in merge_config_file

If we don't single quote the extracted argument to iniset we drop any
quotes from the source.  Add a simple test-case for this.

Partial-bug: #1374118

Change-Id: If2f47b64b11015e727a011c7e5f6e8ad378b90eb

commit_message:
Horizon panel, tabs, and tables for policies

contrib/devstack/lib/
* congress: Copy files needed for Horizon integration.

contrib/horizon/
* _50_policies.py: Configuration for plugin panel.
* congress.py: Wrapper around Congress Python client.
* policies/*: New panel, tabs, and tables for displaying policy details, policy
  rules, and policy tables.

Implements: blueprint horizon-read-policies
Change-Id: I86e75f5fd7db79d8f98b86afb4d6447b298d41e4

commit_message:
Reactivated simulation functionality in policy engine

Previously we had deactivated the ability to simulate
the results of an API call and run a query.

This change reactivates that functionality by syncing it
with updates to the policy engine made since deactivation
and reactivating the tests.

Change-Id: I66b593aa3603147503c92ac7db7ad6c8c1f8122d

commit_message:
Threshold Engine needs the sub alarm id and the alarm sub expression
they map to for AlarmUpdatedEvent and AlarmDeletedEvent

Fully implement equals and hashcode for AlarmUpdatedEvent

Add severity to AlarmDefinitionUpdatedEvent

Make it so MetricDefinition dimensions is an empty map instead
of null if there are no dimensions

Change-Id: Ib1d4b3e7adcdb7ec557c0f07515064127f299927

[{'created': '2014-07-16 13:38:35.000000000', 'message': "Prevent setting swift+config locations

Forbid setting 'swift+config' locations in a similar
manner to 'file' for security reasons; knowledge of
the reference name should not be exploitable.

Setting swift+config had been prevented when swift
was the default store, this patch changes to forbid
setting no matter which store is the default.

As with change id I75af34145521f533dcd6f5fd7690f5a68f3b44b3
this is v1 only for now.

commit_message:
Prevent setting swift+config locations

Forbid setting 'swift+config' locations in a similar
manner to 'file' for security reasons; knowledge of
the reference name should not be exploitable.

Setting swift+config had been prevented when swift
was the default store, this patch changes to forbid
setting no matter which store is the default.

As with change id I75af34145521f533dcd6f5fd7690f5a68f3b44b3
this is v1 only for now.

Change-Id: I62c4980bd5c2f3dd77fc40cd007bc1067eca63a4
Closes-bug: 1334196

commit_message:
Change creation of AlarmUpdatedEvent and AlarmDeletedEvent

Threshold Engine needs the sub alarm id and the alarm sub expression
they map to for AlarmUpdatedEvent and AlarmDeletedEvent

Add new method to AlarmMySqlRepositoryImpl to get the sub alarm info
from the sub_alarm table. Thresh creates the entries in the sub_alarm
table

Fix the AlarmMySqlRepositoryImpl and AlarmDefinitionMySqlRepositoryImpl
unit tests

Send AlarmDeletedEvents for all alarms that get deleted when
an Alarm Definition is deleted

Add severity to the AlarmDefinitionUpdatedEvent

Change-Id: I61c887d5725a76faf3a2fd3b07a53a4f6275ed81

commit_message:
Configures novnc proxy to listen on local-ipv4

Currently novnc proxy listens on all interfaces. This patch changes
it to listen on the host management interface (local-ipv4) like the
rest of the nova services. This is a pre-requisite to making vncproxy
sit behind haproxy and stunnel.

Change-Id: Iba3e35165a1e842ce0fc604ec92ddbd0009e99c2

Make sure that keystonemiddleware package is installed

With I58dad8e1151067bf8df37e511fff5fc0e3dfb487 we switched from

commit_message:
SELinux: Fix keepalived killall denials

A custom policy to temporarily fix the killall denials until the
upstream SELinux policy and keepalived packages are updated.

Change-Id: Ie0d8529d22fc39acaede8a3f1985c50ead76f1f3
Partial-Bug: 1379079

Remove bogus path in tox.ini's flake8 exclude

It referenced os_collect_config's oslo-incubator path, and
os-refresh-config has neither.

The parameter "cumulative" was interpreted as a list and could
not be recognized as a valid Type for SQL query hence failing
to record the data for the pollster.

The presence of ',' operator in the pollster class after the term
CUMULATIVE caused it to be treated as a list

This is corrected to interpret the field as a string which will

commit_message:
Fix recording failure for system pollster

The parameter "cumulative" was interpreted as a list and could
not be recognized as a valid Type for SQL query hence failing
to record the data for the pollster.

The presence of ',' operator in the pollster class after the term
CUMULATIVE caused it to be treated as a list

This is corrected to interpret the field as a string which will
be successfully recorded to the meter database.

Change-Id: I10a69134a7f0c42a3e6c0d9bb7568e8d8fd2a932
Closes-Bug: 1378742

commit_message:
Enable support for software component

The group property indicates whether it is softwarecomponent or plain
softwareconfig.
If it is softwarecomponent, recognizes 'configs' section in metadata,
and choose a proper config to invoke depending on the 'deploy_action'
value.

Partially implements: blueprint action-aware-sw-config

Change-Id: I503032ed09fb5448da225c53c690543fa30d957f

This also doesn't make clear that the original ignore was E12, E711, and I think that's what we'd like to get back to. And if not, that the other ignores that we end up with, are because we decided that we wanted to ignore them.

[{'created': '2014-10-09 18:38:17.000000000', 'message': 'Fix pep8 test

For hacking 0.9 "ignore" and "select" options are mutually exclusive,
therefore pep8 test always passed. This patch fix this bug and also
fix long line in keystone module.

Closes-Bug: #1379470
Change-Id: Ie8681caa9891bc4f4e257a8e56dc4a30c6f26723
'}]
commit_message:
Fix pep8 test

For hacking 0.9 "ignore" and "select" options are mutually exclusive,
therefore pep8 test always passed. This patch fix this bug and also
fix long line in keystone module.

Closes-Bug: #1379470
Change-Id: Ie8681caa9891bc4f4e257a8e56dc4a30c6f26723

commit_message:
Cisco N1kv: Remove vmnetwork delete REST call on last port delete

Remove the vm network delete call to the VSM on final port call and
ensure that vm network is deleted from the database when the port count
becomes 0.

Change-Id: I6c08a099adfce2fdba8eefec6aadeb68a780ac37
Closes-Bug: 1373547

Use new style classes everywhere

Old style classes has been deprecated and should not be used
anymore

https://docs.python.org/2/reference/datamodel.html#new-style-and-classic-classes

Change-Id: I8f85f5a63af7c6500d6efcde5efe8a1fd1456ff0
Closes-Bug: #1378021

commit_message:
Moved exceptions.py and utils.py up to plugins dir

Plugins dir contains 'general' module which looks like yet another
plugin along with vanilla, fake, hdp, spark and cdh. But it doesn't
and contains two files only. Moved them one level up to avoid such
confusion.

Closes-Bug: #1378178

Change-Id: Ia600e4c584d48a3227552f0051cc3bf906206bed

'}, {'account_id': 1179, 'date': '2013-08-02 17:40:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Please reference the associated blueprint for this feature in the commit message.  Is there any information online from a design discussion in Portland that I apparently missed?  How does this change effect existing deployments and auth systems?  What is "ACP"?

Victor,

It's not immediately obvious to me why swift containers should support these properties.  I'm assuming you have a use case which requires a higher degree of granularity than is available in tempauth today - but I'd really like to see those needs enumerated so I could evaluate the trade offs of supporting this new container metadata, against this one possible solution.

Were any alternative approaches discussed/attempted?  This feels like it's pushing a great bit of domain specific detail for authz decisions down into swift's guts - do we want to handle all this down there?  Could the authz middleware strip the body or headers off a container listing based on the return of a custom parse_acl?

When you add a new auth feature to swift, reviewers will need a reference implementation to evaluate it (you can't really judge the correctness of the interface without a user, and auth needs to be correct).  If you have a 3rd part auth system built to this specification - you could offer that.  Or sometimes reviewers can write something up on their own as part of the review and make it available after the merge (but it's a bit of extra work).  Typically this means submitters will include support in tempauth with any new auth related change.

tl;dr

Step #0 for new feature - describe the use case'}, {'account_id': 2401, 'date': '2013-08-02 18:19:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Hello. This patch is draft.

You are right, I will create blueprint for this patch.

ACP is access control permission.

This changes will work with tempauth and keystone auth middlewares. Deployments that use X-Container-Read and X-Container-Write headers will work as before.

The main idea of this patch is to make swift ACL more compatible with AWS S3 ACL (http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/UsingACLsandBucketPoliciesTogether.html).'}, {'account_id': 1179, 'date': '2013-08-02 18:48:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: No score

Thanks for the blueprint.  S3 does it so it must be a good idea right?  </me cries inside>

I think I see how this works, and I understand *now* how it is backwards compatible.  Is it confusing that x-container-read is *always* stripped from headers, even though it grants you the x-container-acl-read-acp permission?

This change needs some new tests.  Tests would also help demonstrate how to use and document usecase.  I suggest functional tests, i.e. test/functionalnosetests/test_container.py - look for tests with "use_account".

Docs too - doc/source/overview_auth.rst

Why not do the ACL-Write work in this same patch?  You can just do it in container POST probably?  I don't think any one will really be interested in merging half finished solution, but I understand not wanting to do work for nothing if no one wants the feature.

I think it looks like ok feature.  I personally would have liked to see account level ACL's done - I'm worried adding this would make account ACL's more complicated?  And this is less valuable to me.

The commit message says:

    X-Container-ACL-Read:
        This permission allow user only read list of objects
        in container.

... but you want that to also download objects too... and then instead of blunt X-Container-Read, we recommend X-Container-ACL-Read which does *not* grant X-Container-ACL-Read-ACP (I'm not sure X-Container-ACL-Read-ACP actually grants X-Container-ACL-Read-ACP if you consider X-Container-Read a valid Access Control Policy?  see inline)

Finial thought: do we need so many horrible acronyms?  Access Control List *and* Access Control Policy - so many meaningless words! commit_message:
Extended container ACL headers

This patch add new type of headers to container server:

    X-Container-ACL-Read:
        This permission allow user only read list of objects
        in container.

    X-Container-ACL-Read-ACP:
        This permission allow user get list of ACL headers
        from container, but not list of objects in container.

    X-Container-ACL-Write (not implemented):
        This permission allow user change container metadata
        and upload objects to container.

    X-Container-ACL-Write-ACP (not implemented):
        This permission allow user change container ACL
        headers.

So current acl header X-Container-Read splited into X-Container-ACL-Read
and X-Container-ACL-Read-ACP.

The same for the X-Container-Write ACL header.

Implements: blueprint extend-container-acl-headers
Change-Id: Ia86f8b9b8886cc53ab6bb58cf117fe4c8d2a3903

commit_message:
Add missing extra "greenthread" arg to remove_event()

See: http://eventlet.net/doc/modules/greenthread.html
the callback gets passed a "gt" arg.

Closes-bug: #1379072

commit_message:
Allow hostname for nodes in Ring

    This change modifies the swift-ring-builder so that hostnames
    can be used in place of an ip-address for the add node command.
    The account reaper, container synchronizer, and replicators
    were also updated so that they still have a way to identify
    a particular device as being "local".

    Previously this was Change-Id: Ic3fbbd0a3cfc4d685a18eb33d8639665a2ce089a

Change-Id: Ie471902413002872fc6755bacd36af3b9c613b74

commit_message:
Clean up Account ACL sysmeta in AccountController

The real account-server never responds with sysmeta to PUT and POST requests, but
the proxy's AccountController code seemed to assume it did - had unittests
that mocked out the responses and everything.  This change brings the code and
tests back inline with reality.

Also stream line and attempt to simply some of the Account ACL Sysmeta
processing logic in the AccountController along the way - no functional
changes there, but I did consolidate a couple of call sites for
get_sys_meta_prefix('account') + 'core-access-control' to just a module level
constant for the 'X-Account-Sysmeta-Core-Access-Control' header.

Change-Id: I88208cbee79ed6e88269c0c7c65f6a02a0e91037

commit_message:
Harden v2 common.middleware.acl interface

The goal of this change is to:

 * simplify the interface contract for the Account ACL methods.
 * better isolate and highlight as a guideline in TempAuth where custom
   Account ACL syntax would be applied.
 * better document the interface.

Change-Id: I88ca831e04819f81e2604f8db627d4c9da87f047

Fix tox.ini to work with latest tox

Without this, I get:

  tox.ConfigError: ConfigError: substitution key 'posargs' not found

on running tox.

Closes-Bug: 1341343

commit_message:
Adds tty password entry for swiftclient

Added functionality from keystoneclient to fallback to the tty for password
entry if no password is given via the environment or the --os-password option.

Change-Id: I9bf1f70dd4cdd25467587a416df9631ed4ce980a
Closes-Bug: 1357562

commit_message:
Queue's empty list should return 200 and an object

The queue's endpoint is not consistent with the rest of the API nor with
the API specs. It currently returns 204 and no response when there are
no queue's in the system. Instead, it should return 200 OK and an object
with an empty `queues` list.

Closes-bug: #1379220
Change-Id: Ib3af5ef3829cc82f3e96bb5401f71b7599f5c5c8

commit_message:
DO NOT MERGE: see what happens with tempest if we don't set quotas

We used to disable rate limiting in the gate for Tempest runs, so why do
we run with quota limits?  Let's see what happens if we turn those off.

Related-Bug: #1353962

Change-Id: I8bfc403351df074698628a93ae5e984db35c5c23

commit_message:
Support a common cache for metadata

Currently, the Nova metadata API stores its cache in memory, which
prevents it from being shared amongst multiple hypervisors and thus
reduces the hit rate. This blueprint proposes to optionally replace
the in-memory cache with the new oslo.cache, allowing cache sharing
between hypervisors.

Change-Id: Ife6beb8508522ef334cc21d11f82380e87a2963c

I'm not against this change, but I'd like to clarify something and then discuss first.

There is a mistake in the implementation, but the intent was actually for message to be set on the InstanceAction model not the event.  In nova/db/sqlalchemy/api.py:action_event_finish() you'll see that message is updated with a hardcoded string and that's where the message from compute utils should go.  I see no harm in storing it on the event as well, though it's slightly redundant.  But it was conceived as a way to propagate info to the user facing InstanceAction and hide the traceback in the admin visible InstanceActionEvent."}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2014-02-07 06:03:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Abandoned

Nothing to do here, abandoning change.'}]

commit_message:
Add "message" column to InstanceActionEvent class

nova.compute.utils.EventReporter expects InstanceActionEvent objects
to have a property named "message", and it populates one on errors.
Make the back-end match this assumption.

Closes-Bug: 1261565
Change-Id: Ifbe82877f12a255142adf58c0ed172cfe981b167

commit_message:
Add ability to manage Neutron ML2 plugin package state

Introduce the package_ensure parameter to add the ability
to manage Neutron ML2 plugin package state.

Conflicts:
  manifests/plugins/ml2.pp

Closes-bug: #1355370
Change-Id: I3bf6ed68015c13cf61db1b43dfbf4fd3c845d00f
(cherry picked from commit 7d20fc90ed75fbb6fd61a92254e5b0ca32475b31)

[{'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-08-11 20:39:06.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-11 20:39:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

http://status.openstack.org/zuul/'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-12 00:26:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

Build succeeded.

- gate-openstack-doc-tools-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/67/113367/1/check/gate-openstack-doc-tools-pep8/f4842be : SUCCESS in 2m 34s'}, {'account_id': 11109, 'date': '2014-08-12 07:50:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

So far, jsoncheck.py could be used as a stand-alone, self-contained tool.

On a system with Python installed, a copy of jsoncheck.py was sufficient to check and fix JSON files. I found that useful.

With this patch, I get the benefit of an error message telling me "ImportError: No module named oslo.config".

I can't say I'm thrilled, but it seems the way OpenStack goes, so no -1 from me.'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-08-12 18:06:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Roger, I think the usage of oslo should be preferred. If you install openstack-doc-tools using pip it should be possible to use jsoncheck.py by calling openstack-jsoncheck. oslo.config is a requirement of openstack-doc-tools and should be installed by pip.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-12 18:19:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Starting check jobs.
http://status.openstack.org/zuul/'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-08-12 18:19:17.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 11109, 'date': '2014-08-12 18:43:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Say I make a change (or check one out via git review -d), and I would like to test jsoncheck.py. What's the preferred way to do that now?"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-12 19:44:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

Build failed.  For information on how to proceed, see https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/GerritJenkinsGit#Test_Failures

- gate-openstack-doc-tools-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/67/113367/2/check/gate-openstack-doc-tools-pep8/bff5768 : FAILURE in 3m 08s'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-08-13 06:28:11.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-13 06:28:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Starting check jobs.
http://status.openstack.org/zuul/'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-08-13 06:28:37.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-13 06:28:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Starting check jobs.
http://status.openstack.org/zuul/'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-13 06:30:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified+1

Build succeeded.

- gate-openstack-doc-tools-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/67/113367/4/check/gate-openstack-doc-tools-pep8/bdb9b1c : SUCCESS in 2m 11s'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-08-13 06:31:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Roger there are several ways. First you install the package "oslo.config" with "pip install oslo.config". Then it should be possible to call "python os_doc_tools/jsoncheck.py". To test for PEP8 issues you can simply call "tox -e pep8".

It's also possible to use a virtual environment. Initialize it inside the repository with "virtualenv name_of_the_venv" and initialize it with "source name_of_the_venv/bin/activate". Now you can install openstack-doc-tools with "python setup.py install" inside this virtual environemnt with all needed requirements (including oslo.config).'}, {'account_id': 11109, 'date': '2014-08-13 07:57:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

The instructions you give illustrate my point. Neither of them work. One is incorrect, the other incomplete. Now _I_ know how to make them work, but I had sort of hoped that we are creating tools that can be used by normal people outside of a carefully crafted CI environment.'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-08-13 08:05:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Why are they incomplete or do not work for you?'}, {'account_id': 11109, 'date': '2014-08-13 10:27:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

"python setup.py install" takes more than half a minute on a pretty decent workstation, and that's _after_ installing all kinds of development libraries needed to build. Even then, on a current Debian system I had to update pip itself before setup.py was able to install the required version of oslo.config ("Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement oslo.config>=1.4.0.0a3"). And _then_ "openstack-jsoncheck" yields "ImportError: No module named pbr.version". This is an awful way to do development testing.

Now the other method, "python os_doc_tools/jsoncheck.py", used to work (and still does on master). But with the patch under review, after installing the latest version of oslo.config, I get an error "ImportError: No module named os_doc_tools".'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-08-13 10:32:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Roger, I think that we should not implement standalone scripts inside a Python package. When you install the package "openstack-doc-tools" and use the binary "openstack-jsoncheck" everything should work like expected. Using "python setup.py install", calling the script manually with "python os_doc_tools/jsoncheck.py" and the other described ways are only for developers and not for the daily usage.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-18 18:53:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified-1

Merge Failed.

This change was unable to be automatically merged with the current state of the repository. Please rebase your change and upload a new patchset.'}, {'account_id': 612, 'date': '2014-10-03 05:30:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Hi, just pinging this, wondering where this is at, or whether this patch should be abandoned?'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-10-09 20:34:20.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

I think this change is not correct, base is the correct.

There is no other part which are using weighter/Weighter, although both weight and weigh are used.'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-09-04 06:05:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I changed it to 'weights' (ht) because the class is part of cinder.scheduler.weights. The class itself is called VolumeNumberWeigher which looks wrong to me because of cinder.scheduler.weights. There are some docstrings already using 'weights'. Some names are using 'weight' (volume_number_weight_opts, _weight_multiplier) and some are using 'weigh' (_weigh_object, VolumeNumberWeigher) at the moment."}, {'account_id': 9533, 'date': '2014-09-05 05:20:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

Thanks for your explanation.
I understood.'}, {'account_id': 964, 'date': '2014-09-05 13:29:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I believe weight is the noun form, weigh is the verb form, and weighter is not a word. (Weigher is a word, much to my surprise, meaning "someone/something who/that weighs.)

So I think the original docstrings are more grammatically accurate, however, when the option is named scheduler_default_weighters then it's difficult to document because weighters is not a word.

Can the option name be changed from scheduler_default_weighters to scheduler_default_weighers before Feature Freeze?'}, {'account_id': 167, 'date': '2014-10-09 20:33:39.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Replace admin@example.org with admin@localhost

Puppet manifest configures account under Admin/Identity Panel/Users
with email address of admin@example.org.  To prevent
sending unwarranted messages to admin.org domain,
replacing that with admin@localhost.

Change-Id: I5635c0af30227c2b601b352a4d9dff9a40fa0917
Closes-Bug: 1372336

commit_message:
Calculate a suitable column width for positional arguments

Overwrite the method add_arguments in the class
OpenStackHelpFormatter to calculate a suitable columnt width
(max_help_position) for the positional arguments.

example output before this patch:

    qos-disassociate-all
                        Disassociates qos specs from all associations.
    qos-get-association
                        Gets all associations for specified qos specs.

example output after this patch:

    qos-disassociate              Disassociates qos specs from specified
                                  volume type.
    qos-disassociate-all          Disassociates qos specs from all
                                  associations.

commit_message:
Add v1 image update unicode test

This adds a test where an image with a unicode name is updated to make
sure that the encoding is handled properly through the request and
response.

commit_message:
Do not try to show changes of non-master branches

If the current branch is not set to master, report the branch and do not
report any changes to avoid giving a misleading impression of a
potential release.

Change-Id: I12a4f655339721f751b04cdef0cc689bd3485d42

commit_message:
Change clone_openstack.sh to ignore stackforge by default

Oslo projects will not be in stackforge, so we can ignore those by
default and save time and space.

Change-Id: Ia01e23cc4d38f4a5de06919495873fe57975d444

commit_message:
Set up for kilo specs

This adds the entries in the index so that the main page will
list the specs in specs/kilo. To get sphinx to not err, a dummy
.rst file (based on the template.rst) was added to specs/kilo.
It should be deleted after we have an approved spec.

Without this temporary fix, all spec patches will basically
need to have the change in index.rst; otherwise Jenkins will
not be happy.

Note that the dummy .rst file needs to be added or sphinx will
complain because the specs/kilo/* pattern didn't match any
documents. Furthermore, the .rst file there must be valid
(based on the template) or the unit tests will fail. And lastly,
that dummy .rst file cannot be named 'template.rst' because
we've configured it to ignore all files named 'template.rst'. If
that is ignored, we're back to no files in specs/kilo, and sphinx
will be unhappy again.

Closes-Bug: #1379415
Change-Id: Ic4a40a5b085073bc9eebc3d2c75432f18f01cbef

commit_message:
Queue's empty list should return 200 and an object

The queue's endpoint is not consistent with the rest of the API nor with
the API specs. It currently returns 204 and no response when there are
no queue's in the system. Instead, it should return 200 OK and an object
with an empty `queues` list.

Closes-bug: #1379220
Change-Id: Ib3af5ef3829cc82f3e96bb5401f71b7599f5c5c8

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-12 20:46:57.000000000', 'message': "Stop using intersphinx

Remove intersphinx from the docs build as it triggers network calls that
occasionally fail, and we don't really use intersphinx (links other
sphinx documents out on the internet)

This also removes the requirement for internet access during docs build.

This causes docs jobs to fail because we error out on warnings.

Change-Id: I71e941e2a639641a662a163c682eb86d51de42fb
Related-Bug: #1368910
"}]
commit_message:
Stop using intersphinx

Remove intersphinx from the docs build as it triggers network calls that
occasionally fail, and we don't really use intersphinx (links other
sphinx documents out on the internet)

This also removes the requirement for internet access during docs build.

This causes docs jobs to fail because we error out on warnings.

Change-Id: I71e941e2a639641a662a163c682eb86d51de42fb
Related-Bug: #1368910

commit_message:
Truncate fail_reason to column length

During create_backup failure handling, backup_update fails with
DataError ("Data too long for column") if the fail_reason is
greater than 255 characters. As a result, backup status is stuck
in 'creating' state. This patch avoids the problem by truncating
fail_reason to 255 characters before update.

Closes-Bug: #1376199
Change-Id: If0d616b81d3869f7ea110caab8cf4140cf5c5c9e

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-10-07 20:15:10.000000000', 'message': "Break out over-quota calculation code from quota_reserve()

The list comprehension used to create the overs list was really hard to
read, so this moves that code into it's own helper method and breaks out
the logic from the list comprehension, and adds unit tests.

This changes the logic a bit in that rather than check project/user
quotas/usages for each resource, we only check project quotas/usages for
resources in PER_PROJECT_QUOTAS, since they shouldn't have user
quotas/usages (or should at least be identical to the project
quotas/usages).

Partial-Bug: #1369605

Change-Id: I44236c7a206b2a9bd3843c9ca2ce56591a66352f

"}]
commit_message:
Break out over-quota calculation code from quota_reserve()

The list comprehension used to create the overs list was really hard to
read, so this moves that code into it's own helper method and breaks out
the logic from the list comprehension, and adds unit tests.

Partial-Bug: #1369605

Change-Id: I44236c7a206b2a9bd3843c9ca2ce56591a66352f

commit_message:
Adding support for oslo.rootwrap to namespace access

Changes
* adding configuration options for rootwrap
* refactoring ssh connection to use rootwrap as a proxy when requested
* adding documentation for rootwrap configuration
* adding default rootwrap filters file
* adding default sudoers conf file for sahara user
* adding default rootwrap conf file for sahara-rootwrap
* adding sahara-rootwrap cli script
* adding requirement for oslo.rootwrap

Change-Id: I7871400b2342a4cd1a8910ae5121b1bfdc46078d
Closes-Bug: #1271349

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-10-09 17:32:53.000000000', 'message': 'PowerDNS schema should cascade domain deletes

When a domain is deleted, we should cascade the delete into the
records and domainmetadata tables. This is required for an mDNS
based PowerDNS backend to function without knowledge of the
records etc tables.

Change-Id: Iac2fadabd8e101fc0b8267d612cb18ba44a30e6b
'}]
commit_message:
PowerDNS schema should cascade domain deletes

When a domain is deleted, we should cascade the delete into the
records and domainmetadata tables. This is required for an mDNS
based PowerDNS backend to function without knowledge of the
records etc tables.

Change-Id: Iac2fadabd8e101fc0b8267d612cb18ba44a30e6b

commit_message:
Change labels in QOS Specs panels

Under Admin->Volumes->Volume Types, all the QOS spec
forms and tables should match the Cinder docs, which
use "QoS", instead of "QOS".

Also, references to QoS "consumer" should be
capitalized.

Change-Id: I70237152732f02c4c2c6c34917181a5dcb669b12
Closes-Bug: #1371711

commit_message:
Set barbican host_href param to $SERVICE_HOST on devstack

Default barbican host_href config value has 'localhost' as the host
which will be part of secret_ref uri. On devstack, barbican registers
$SERVICE_HOST as its host in keystone and that doesn't resolve to
localhost on F20 when someone authenticates with keystone.
Pointing barbican host_href to $SERVICE_HOST solves the issue.

Closes-Bug: #1371252
Change-Id: I6269189565b487afaa1330b364e0d6fea2131b55

commit_message:
Improvements to the dashboard installation section

Improved dashboard content in the installation guide as
follows:

1) Restructured steps for consistency with similar sections.
2) Updated list of packages to install.
3) Adjusted configuration on all distributions to use memcached
   for session storage to simplify installation.
4) Clarified instructions for access permissions.
5) Split verification step into separate section for consistency
   with other chapters.
6) Changed removal of Ubuntu theme package from 'required' to
   'optional' based on user experience.
7) Added workaround for RDO packaging issues.

This patch includes changes for Juno.

Change-Id: Iecb1cff57853b097ba2ee0a5016438190ff8d920
Implements: blueprint installation-guide-improvements
Co-Authored-By: Matt Kassawara <mkassawara@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Don't edit commit history with migrate from tempest tool

This commit changes the migrate_from_tempest tool to not mess around
with the commit history. The previous approach in the tool isn't
actually something that we can do. The commit history we had when the
repository was created is the canonical past for tempest-lib and we
can't migrate over any other tempest commits directly, this was a
mistake on my part.

Moving forward we'll just have to refer to the commit sha1s from the
tempest repo in the commit message. This script will now just copy the
specified files from tempest and generate a commit message with the
complete list of sha1s from the tempest history.

Change-Id: I7e2b2a0543d113961598b33d23985a1082fbba9a

commit_message:
Fix pci_request_id break the upgrade from icehouse to juno

commit a8a5d44c8aca218f00649232c2b8a46aee59b77e add pci_request_id
as one item for the request_network tuple. But the icehouse code
assume only three items in the tuple.

This patch filters pci_request_id out from the tuple.

Cherry-Pick from:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/126144/6

Change-Id: I991e1c68324fe92fac647583f3ec8f6aec637913
Closes-Bug: #1377447

commit_message:
Remove two sets that are not referenced

The code no longer references the updated_routers and removed_routers
sets.  This should have been cleaned up before but was missed.

Change-Id: I0396e13d2f7c3789928e0c6a4c0a071b02d5ff17

commit_message:
Rename deployer delete_heat_stack to destroy

It doesn't make any sense that all deployers regardless of
their use of heat should have a method naming heat.
This patch renames the method to the more generic 'destroy',
and also adds the missing method to deployer's noop handler.
Without the method noop was in violation of its API.

Change-Id: Ia525678055a40474413dbe2f4a5a062da7d92121
Closes-Bug: 1350579

commit_message:
Stop using intersphinx

Remove intersphinx from the docs build as it triggers network calls that
occasionally fail, and we don't really use intersphinx (links other
sphinx documents out on the internet)

This also removes the requirement for internet access during docs build.

This can cause docs jobs to fail if the project errors out on
warnings.

Change-Id: I71e941e2a639641a662a163c682eb86d51de42fb
Related-Bug: #1368910

While RDBMS'es recommend not using reserved words as identifiers, some still support it. For example, with MySQL it allows you to use keywords as column names, but, you have to prefix the column with the table name - Examples: Create table tablex (id int, tablex.schema Text);  Select id, alia.schema from tablex as alia. My assumption is, since SQLAlchemy doesn't complain, that it - or the MySQL driver in SQLAlchemy is doing the needful to (always?) prefix column names with the table name. commit_message:
Metadef schema column name is a reserved word in MySQL

The metadef_properties and metadef_objects tables both have
a column named schema. Unfortunately, schema is a reserved word
in some relational database products, including MySQL and PostgreSQL.
The metadef_properties.schema and metadef_objects.schema
columns should be renamed to a non reserved word.

Change-Id: I9c1b497d2b09b9282a83bd8c19c32edfa4dd159f
Closes-Bug: 1378968

Thanks for keeping this going...I need to spend more time with it to understand everything, I'm not very familiar with the auth plugins yet.  Some early notes:

* Thanks for the working example of using a ksc session, Jamie wasn't thrilled with what I was trying to do.  Would it be possible to split out the session bits and just select v2/v3 password based on the existing API selection?

* I would prefer to disconnect the auth plugin selection from the identity version if possible, I don't think most users will know/care which API version they use and I'd rather not add that if possible.

* It looks like the auth plugins are specifying user-visible parts, ie the word 'tenant' in places.  We've nearly eradicated that word from a user's view and I'd like to keep it that way.  That's the reason for the Identity client subclasses.

* We already use mock and I'm ok with adding requests-mock, but do we really need mox3 too?"}, {'account_id': 7186, 'date': '2014-08-22 11:23:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

(2 comments)

@Dean,
Concerning your notes:

* I am not sure I understand "split out the session bits", what do you mean ?
* I guess that's possible, provided plugins keep the naming convention of vXpluginname. They should care about the API version, though, since from one version to another the same method might need different parameters.
* I see your point, but this is the way it is defined and expected by the v2 plugins ... "tenant" is after all the historical term for the v2 API. I guess we could filter out the tenant-related options when listing plugin options, if you think it is worth the effort.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-23 11:07:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: Verified-1

(1 comment)

The old authentication options are still there and behave as usual. New options are introduced automatically as needed by new authentication plugins. The only notable change is that you need to specify --os-auth-plugin=token to authenticate with a token (not applicable to service token auth, as it is filtered through the --os-url option). Actually the gate tests used to fail when the patch broke compatibility ...


On the other hand, the 'token' and 'password' generic plugins have been introduced in python-keystoneclient 0.11, so either the global requirements need to be updated ( https://review.openstack.org/#/c/124633/ ) or I can revert the default plugin to 'v2password' if you wish."}, {'account_id': 7186, 'date': '2014-09-28 22:48:52.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 17.'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2014-09-28 23:31:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 17:

I missed that OS_AUTH_PLUGIN was required for a v3 pw auth.  We can't add that requirement at this point.  (BTW, we need a known Identity v3 config to use for verification in, say, Steve's new functional tests.)

At a minimum we need to continue to follow the existing logic if determining the default auth combination based on presence of url/token info (although I think using _token is more reliable than _url) and selecting the version based on the requested/default Identity client version.

In the future (soon?) we should be able to let ksc do the auth version selection, although it still doesn't work with some broken default configurations.

FWIW, I'm not very concerned with the exact look of the auth options as long as previously valid combinations still work.

Anyway, this (https://github.com/stackforge/os-client-config) is coming down the road soon now that it is in stackforge and will change again the way options are handled internally so this review isn't the final word anyway.  I had a wonderfully working candidate solution last Sunday, unfortunately I can't just push in a big-ole patch like that. ;)"}, {'account_id': 7186, 'date': '2014-09-28 23:31:40.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 18.'}, {'account_id': 6482, 'date': '2014-09-29 01:18:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17:

This patch allows the user to choose which authentication plugin
to use with the CLI. The arguments needed by the auth plugins are
automatically added to the argument parser. Some examples with
the currently available authentication plugins::

  OS_USERNAME=admin OS_PROJECT_NAME=admin OS_AUTH_URL=http://keystone:5000/v2.0 \
  OS_PASSWORD=admin openstack user list

  OS_USERNAME=admin OS_PROJECT_DOMAIN_NAME=default OS_USER_DOMAIN_NAME=default \
  OS_PROJECT_NAME=admin OS_AUTH_URL=http://keystone:5000/v3 OS_PASSWORD=admin \
  OS_IDENTITY_API_VERSION=3 OS_AUTH_PLUGIN=v3password openstack project list

  OS_TOKEN=1234 OS_URL=http://service_url:35357/v2.0 \
  OS_IDENTITY_API_VERSION=2.0 openstack user list

commit_message:
Support for keystone auth plugins

This patch allows the user to choose which authentication plugin
to use with the CLI. The arguments needed by the auth plugins are
automatically added to the argument parser. Some examples with
the currently available authentication plugins::

  OS_USERNAME=admin OS_PROJECT_NAME=admin OS_AUTH_URL=http://keystone:5000/v2.0 \
  OS_PASSWORD=admin openstack user list

  OS_USERNAME=admin OS_PROJECT_DOMAIN_NAME=default OS_USER_DOMAIN_NAME=default \
  OS_PROJECT_NAME=admin OS_AUTH_URL=http://keystone:5000/v3 OS_PASSWORD=admin \
  OS_IDENTITY_API_VERSION=3 OS_AUTH_PLUGIN=v3password openstack project list

  OS_TOKEN=1234 OS_URL=http://service_url:35357/v2.0 \
  OS_IDENTITY_API_VERSION=2.0 openstack user list

The --os-auth-plugin option can be omitted; if so the CLI will attempt to
guess which plugin to use from the other options.

Change-Id: I330c20ddb8d96b3a4287c68b57c36c4a0f869669
Co-Authored-By: Florent Flament <florent.flament-ext@cloudwatt.com>

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-10-07 15:35:09.000000000', 'message': 'Fix eqlx CLI output parsing on bad input

The eqlx driver would identify CLI command completion
by looking for the system name prompt at the end of
the output ("ARRAY_NAME>"). In some cases where there
is bad input the array will print an error, then
prepopulate the command again so it can be edited,
resulting in the output:

"ARRAY_NAME> [bad command]"

The array name prompt only gets printed on command
completion, so the fix is to look for the prompt
anywhere in the CLI output.

Change-Id: I063a203c9746689ca8a42a97725b059f782e3812
Closes-Bug: 1378394

commit_message:
Fix eqlx CLI output parsing on bad input

The eqlx driver would identify CLI command completion
by looking for the system name prompt at the end of
the output ("ARRAY_NAME>"). In some cases where there
is bad input the array will print an error, then
prepopulate the command again so it can be edited,
resulting in the output:

"ARRAY_NAME> [bad command]"

The array name prompt only gets printed on command
completion, so the fix is to look for the prompt
anywhere in the CLI output.

Change-Id: I063a203c9746689ca8a42a97725b059f782e3812
Closes-Bug: 1378394

commit_message:
Eqlx fix NoSuchOptError for volume_name_template on clone

The eqlx driver was referencing the volume_name_template
config setting via self.configuration.volume_name_template.
This option is not imported in self.configuration.

The curent preferred method for volume clone is to reference
the passed in name, avoiding the need for the driver to
know what the naming template is all together.

Change-Id: If4963bbe61574c006ad04e5e88d04c7f7bc7cee1
Closes-Bug: 1378369

commit_message:
Fix image upload for tar kernel/initrd images

Current logic is parsing output from glance to get the 'id' of the
kernel and initrd images.  Glance command output format was changed long ago
to a table style output and broke this.
There is already a todo in the code to refactor this but I did not attempt
that here.  Also add a todo for more provider method testers.

Change-Id: I68affe1d7f3df2ee69717641f5be6ba16615654e
Closes-Bug: #1373614

commit_message:
Remove stale chunks when failed to update image to registry

For image v1 api, the operation of uploading image bits to store and
the operation of updating image metadata are separaed, so when the
second operation failed, the image stale chunks will be leaked in store.
This change added a logic to remove those chunks if an exception
happenned during the step of image metadata updating. And if
glance-registry could be reached still, the image status will be changed
to 'killed', this followed standard glance image status transition.

Closes-bug: 1254497
Change-Id: I01e13066b48a8feb1ead0de64992e7997feafdea
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

commit_message:
Handle non-existing *generic kernel and initrd

Finding the Debian boot kernel and initrd is collapsed into a
single statement so that the script doesn't bail out when
'set -o pipefail' is set and the *generic kernel and initrd are
absent.

Change-Id: Ifd616818f7387e6f102636c7cf186be6097f1d5c
Closes-Bug: 1335016

Hello, I have been working on sidebar restyling (part of https://blueprints.launchpad.net/openstack/?searchtext=navigation-styling) and got pointed by Aaron to this patch. Getting the sidebar 100% height is interesting problem and so far I think the best solution is to use css flexbox. Unfortunately, it probably does not match our browser support policy (http://caniuse.com/#feat=flexbox).

So as my initial patch used same technique as Thai used, In second revision I used good old body background technique which is IMHO the best solution for the problem at the moment. Please test the patch to see it working flawlessly:)(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/126289/)

@Thai, what do you think about closing this one and resolve the issue as part of my patch?

Btw. the issue of navigation scrolling with the viewport is caused by it's position:fixed. this can be solved by setting  it position:absolute. But it does not get us rid of other issues like unnecessary scrollbar appearing in sidebar and other 100% height vs window height issues."}, {'account_id': 7509, 'date': '2014-10-08 11:36:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: Code-Review-1'}, {'account_id': 9576, 'date': '2014-10-09 16:16:42.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

commit_message:
Add support for redis-sentinel

This patch adds the ability to configure Sentinel support in
zaqar.conf. The code has been tested using one and two sentinels
managing one master and one slave. Failovers from master to slave
were intiated and it was verified that clients can continue to
query the service with no downtime in the case of a lost Redis
node.

Co-Authored-By: Kurt Griffiths <kurt.griffiths@rackspace.com>
Closes-Bug: 1367020
Change-Id: Idcaaab3ba17c84a31b918ad8376f1d5fc105b53a

This patch adds an reliability enforcement for mongodb's driver. It
forces deployers to use replicasets or mongos as a mongodb cluster for
Zaqar. In addition to that, it forces deployers to provide a write
concern > 2 and/or majority.

If none of this are met, the driver will raise a RuntimeException and
fail to start. If no write concern is provided, majority will be used.

commit_message:
Add first reliability enforcement

This patch adds an reliability enforcement for mongodb's driver. It
forces deployers to use replicasets or mongos as a mongodb cluster for
Zaqar. In addition to that, it forces deployers to provide a write
concern > 2 and/or majority.

If none of this are met, the driver will raise a RuntimeException and
fail to start. If no write concern is provided, majority will be used.

Change-Id: Ie74a4b441654243b3ed7e7fd6c40863969cd446d
Closes-bug: #1372335
(cherry picked from commit a1163331fcb3253ae6af5e4cb8c528eb3679baf1)

commit_message:
g-api raises 500 error while uploading image

If both filesystem_store_datadirs and filesystem_store_datadir parameters
specified in glance-api.conf file then while creating new image 500
internal server error is raised.

Caught StoreAddDisabled exception for v1 and v2 api while uploading
image and raised HTTPGone exception to return HTTP 410 response to
user.

Closes-Bug: #1372888
Change-Id: Iccbf5b88634d3c956d41e8d8a0126648c64b34eb

commit_message:
Fixes Hyper-V volume mapping issue on reboot

Hyper-V does not manage iSCSI mounted passthrough disks
correctly on reboot in some circumstances where disk
number assignment can change, resulting in instances potentially
booting with the wrong volume attached.

Co-Authored-By: Adelina Tuvenie <atuvenie@cloudbasesolutions.com>
Co-Authored-By: Adrian Bora <abora@cloudbasesolutions.com>

Closes-Bug: #1322926
(cherry picked from commit 50636a881b60f112027494bcd84af66888db8c1c)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/virt/hyperv/test_vmutils.py
	nova/tests/virt/hyperv/test_vmutilsv2.py
	nova/virt/hyperv/vmutils.py
	nova/virt/hyperv/vmutilsv2.py

Change-Id: I99fa75aaa950de2ada8a03bd23c910c3ff810d69

commit_message:
Log quota refresh in_use message at INFO level for logstash

Commit 5aef26496786c02a1ed324bbd2eb0b9994a2018d added the log message to
give some idea when we're unnecessarily refreshing quota usage.

Logstash only collects INFO+ level messages, so bump this to an INFO
level message so we can track gate runs to see if this is actually a
problem.

Related-Bug: #1353962

Change-Id: I60ffa9dbda22e252f290bf316fa2e472d3e92f2f

commit_message:
Pinned apache2 cookbook version

cookbook version of apache2 should be smaller than 2.0.0, since 2.0.0
is not backwards compatible and would break a lot of specs. Did not
cherry-pick the fix from master since this also includes update of berks
to 3.

Change-Id: Ia994006456db435ede31fdc9d98e2062fd8b26e2

[{'created': '2014-10-09 13:42:07.000000000', 'message': 'Fix for Adopt glance.store library in Glance

The store module is removed from glance project and new glance_store
module is created, but the glance project code was not updated
properly for the required changes.

The exception (UnknownScheme) was moved to glance_store, but in
glance image-create api (v1), it still refers to
exception.UnknownScheme in get_store_or_400 method.

Change-Id: I09e78b92d2d44a659412361b4f03b4a988714bf5
Closes-Bug: 1373454
'}]
commit_message:
Fix for Adopt glance.store library in Glance

The store module is removed from glance project and new glance_store
module is created, but the glance project code was not updated
properly for the required changes.

The exception (UnknownScheme) was moved to glance_store, but in
glance image-create api (v1), it still refers to
exception.UnknownScheme in get_store_or_400 method.

Change-Id: I09e78b92d2d44a659412361b4f03b4a988714bf5
Closes-Bug: 1373454

commit_message:
Import translations from Transifex for Juno

* Import ~100% completed translations
  (translations available for 12 languages)
* Update language list in openstack_dashboard settings.py
* Update English POT files
* Update Transifex resource name in .tx/config for Juno.
* Remove compiled message catalogs (Related-Bug: #1196982)

Closes-Bug: #1376542

The instruction on how to compile message catalogs will be
covered by https://review.openstack.org/#/c/126169/
or the installation guide.

Change-Id: Ib36562168009fa34b9818e99154df350678abd4b

commit_message:
clean up base Dockerfile

- run "yum update" after installing RDO repository (to ensure we get any
  package updates from this repository)
- "yum clean" after the "yum update" to prevent yum cache from being
  baked into the image

commit_message:
Exit with error status on failed command

When we detect a failed command we log ERROR but we do not return an
error status. This makes it difficult for programs which may run
os-collect-config to detect whether a run was sucessful.

This only applies to runs which are performed with --one-time argument
as this is a straightforward case.

Change-Id: I168862e8c75c15d1ea405a417908d1284feb7b32

different services.

commit_message:
Fix doc build errors in db/sqlalchemy/models.py

Building the documentation creates errors like:
manila/db/sqlalchemy/models.py:docstring of
manila.db.sqlalchemy.models.relationship:53: ERROR: Unknown interpreted
text role "paramref".

Fixed with changing the import of relationship to orm.relationship.

Change-Id: I51132581c2bf6a4e68a945a972401dbaed517733
Closes-Bug: #1371739

commit_message:
Add extended logging options.

There is a range of extended logging options in Openstack services that use
openstack.common.logger (Ceilometer, Cinder, Heat, Keystone, Nova). Adding
cinder::logging to support them. This change is identical to
<https://review.openstack.org/#/c/113560/> but it applies to puppet-cinder
instead of puppet-ceilometer.

No blueprint/spec, as discussed in the IRC meeting on 08-11-2014.

Change-Id: Id1d4380157e681da9ada2e2647ab285ce3cc40ad
(cherry picked from commit 47765d2080c669fbf27e9014a687a07bb2c0c64e)

[{'created': '2014-10-01 00:12:56.000000000', 'message': 'Add use_multipath_for_image_xfer with E-Series

This change implements the documented best practice to use multipath
with a Cinder deployment leveraging the NetApp E-Series driver by
setting a Cinder configuration setting to ensure that multipath is
appropriately used by the driver.

Change-Id: I4d279ebefc5a1ed935680775c6ea95fa38c1b9ef
'}]
commit_message:
Add use_multipath_for_image_xfer with E-Series

This change implements the documented best practice to use multipath
with a Cinder deployment leveraging the NetApp E-Series driver by
setting a Cinder configuration setting to ensure that multipath is
appropriately used by the driver.

Change-Id: I4d279ebefc5a1ed935680775c6ea95fa38c1b9ef

commit_message:
Ensure nova-common is installed before ceilometer

Ceilometer depends on the nova user and group being
present. This change adds a dependency to nova-common
to ensure that packging will handle the user before
the ceilometer compute agent tries to add user ceilometer
to the nova group.

Fixes bug 1350980

(cherry picked from commit 08fc9d9159cd9eb0830d550abb1058bc2b9b5759)

Conflicts:
	spec/classes/ceilometer_agent_compute_spec.rb

Change-Id: I26dd4e8e4172d777a04d99c7d23c1861714ca079

commit_message:
Pass the project and user to quotas.rollback when cleaning up fixed_ips

The quotas.rollback method takes a project and user kwarg and if not
provided the values are pulled from the context passed in.

Since we get the project and user from the quotas object in
allocate_fixed_ip and use those in the quotas.reserve call, we should
use them in the quotas.rollback call as well.

Related-Bug: #1353962

Change-Id: I214f8e62eb5f885031a50654164b9efefd481c5d

commit_message:
Fix Horizon integration job definition

While job templates need double brackets, for a regular job definition
there should only be one. Also, remove statements that only apply to
job templates.

Change-Id: I31348a2b3d7d7a62844553a0ff7a5afa00aa1f49
Closes-Bug: #1379256

commit_message:
Makes kombu_ssl_* parameters optional when rabbit_use_ssl => true

The kombu_ssl_* parameters should not be required when rabbit_use_ssl => true
Rather, rabbit_use_ssl must be set to true if the kombu_ssl_* parameters are
used.

Change-Id: I7664dda2c66ffb34ceb56ada722574ae0e490f8f
Closes-Bug: 1356083
(cherry picked from commit 957c2120d0ee0b9db08bfddcce996686ba61d97d)

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-10-08 15:37:11.000000000', 'message': 'engine: configure deferred authentication method

The default deferred_auth_method of password is deprecated as of
Icehouse, so although it is still the default, deployers are strongly
encouraged to move to using deferred_auth_method=trusts, which is
planned to become the default for Juno.

* It avoids storing user credentials in the heat database
* It removes the need to provide a password as well as a token on stack create
* It limits the actions the heat service user can perform on a users behalf.

This patch aims to:
* Set deferred_auth_method = trusts in /etc/heat/heat.conf for engine
* Specify the roles to be delegated to the heat service user
   (trusts_delegated_roles in heat.conf, defaults to heat_stack_owner
   which will be referred to in the following instructions. You may wish
   to modify this list of roles to suit your local RBAC policies)
* Create the role(s) in Keystone (optional and enabled by default).

Change-Id: I99eaf29473bc4e70017580b3b340c24093aa0619

commit_message:
engine: configure deferred authentication method

The default deferred_auth_method of password is deprecated as of
Icehouse, so although it is still the default, deployers are strongly
encouraged to move to using deferred_auth_method=trusts, which is
planned to become the default for Juno.

* It avoids storing user credentials in the heat database
* It removes the need to provide a password as well as a token on stack create
* It limits the actions the heat service user can perform on a users behalf.

This patch aims to:
* Set deferred_auth_method = trusts in /etc/heat/heat.conf for engine
* Specify the roles to be delegated to the heat service user
   (trusts_delegated_roles in heat.conf, defaults to heat_stack_owner
   which will be referred to in the following instructions. You may wish
   to modify this list of roles to suit your local RBAC policies)
* Create the role(s) in Keystone (optional and enabled by default).

Change-Id: I99eaf29473bc4e70017580b3b340c24093aa0619

commit_message:
Replace the concept of tenants in the code-base

The following blueprint proposed the removal of the tenant concept in
favor of using the concept of projects, such as it is being used in
Keystone. This is to promote uniformity in the code-base.

Change-Id: I3efe1e2316c662af73a74369d6e1151080417daa

commit_message:
Add cookie-based authentication along with X-Auth-Token

- added jquery.cookie as Bower dependency
- fixed keystone.py middleware to process the cookie and inject X-Auth-Token
  into the request, X-Auth-Token still has priority though
- fixed 401 response format to return iterable (list)
- added test_auth_token for testing both authentication methods

- remove capacity/csv from public URLs (with the new cookie-based
  authentication this download link does not need anymore to be publicly
  accessible -- the X-Auth-Token header was the reason to first make the link
  public).

Change-Id: Iaf64d32e7e03b26d1095eed7c0757bb99be7328b
Implements: blueprint access-control-master-node-improvments
Related-Bug: #1362615
Related-Bug: #1375622
Related-Bug: #1379000

commit_message:
Min version of rubygem-json for nailgun-agent

nailgun-agent fails with rubygem-json 1.6.1.
Version 1.7.7 is a known working version
that can be used.

Closes-Bug: #1379299

commit_message:
Sort inputs and parameters

They're mostly rather higgledy-piggledy at the moment which makes it
quite difficult to compare against files where these are sorted. EG
compute.yaml from I687a00c7dc164ba044f9f2dfca96a02401427855.

commit_message:
Drop crypto/utils

Unable to find any references to projects using this module.
Keystone folks confirmed that they are not using this. So let's
please drop it.

Change-Id: I20f647a338208cef7267316d389adbdf9b73c8f6

commit_message:
Add waiting for samples count

Method 'wait_samples_count' was added, because in CRUD test for samples
sample sometimes is added to DB after checking for its adding.

Change-Id: I6d8e5caa1926c7df07aab6f661a9925294ea1b9a
Closes-bug: #1367319

[{'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2014-10-07 17:53:22.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 1207, 'date': '2014-10-07 18:02:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 4523, 'date': '2014-10-07 18:10:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

IMO only testing whether the dest supports -t none is not the right answer here.  (Though it does "work".)

qemu-img convert's default mode is writeback which issues an fdatasync().  This flushes data on files but fails (silently) on block devices.

Checking this way means we end up using -t none on files, when we are probably better off using the cache and fdatasync() there.

IMO we should do what this patch does, but only after checking whether the dest is a block device.  Let file destinations just use qemu-img defaults.'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2014-10-07 18:23:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

@eharney

Fair point, but given that Cinder is a "Block" service and in MOST cases the device is a Block device I'm not sure I care too much, particularly as it's not an error in the case of a "file".

If it's a big deal and there is any valid concern I'm open to adding the check you mention.'}, {'account_id': 4523, 'date': '2014-10-07 18:37:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Make sure device support Direct before setting

We added '-t none' option to the qemu-img convert operation
in image_utils.py a while back to accomodate a couple of
backend devices that didn't flush writes on disconnect.
(Change: I7a04f683add8c23b9125fe837c4048ccc3ac224d)

The only problem here is that some backend devices don't
support Direct mode and raise an exception and fail when
setting this option.

This patch adds a simple check using dd to see if the dest
supports the Direct flag and only sets '-t none' if the device
does in fact support it.

Additionally it was brought up that even yet other backends
are using file devices not blk devices.  In their case setting
Direct will still work, however it's sub-optimal as qemu-convert
has internal mechanisms to make sure flushing etc are done
correctly and efficiently for those devices.  So to accomodate
that particular use case I'm also adding a check if blk dev
that can be used for determining whether to set Direct for the
qemu-convert process.

Change-Id: I34127ac373ceadcfb6fc2662628b1a91eb7b0046
Closes-Bug: 1375487

commit_message:
Add AMQP conn check for heat-engine ocf

Improve status check by AMQP port connection tracking.
Heat-engine service will be restarted by pacemaker,
if amqp connection is lost. And monitor action will
report fail, unless amqp connection re-established.
Source: https://github.com/madkiss/openstack-resource-agents
0263ab71d319d3c398c5d29c4c0eb261db358ab1

DocImpact
Related blueprint pacemaker-improvements

Change-Id: I0a2246051212332acc40b8a82d42b585188d5d73
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Add AMQP conn check for ceilo-agent-central ocf

Improve status check by AMQP port connection tracking.
Ceilometer-agent-central service will be restarted by
pacemaker, if amqp connection is lost. And monitor action
will report fail, unless amqp connection re-established.
Source: https://github.com/madkiss/openstack-resource-agents
0263ab71d319d3c398c5d29c4c0eb261db358ab1

DocImpact
Related blueprint pacemaker-improvements

Change-Id: I733e9473bda767c6396a63336c5e6b7ac6415fff
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Add Barbican wrapper specification

This specification supports the following blueprint:
  https://blueprints.launchpad.net/cinder/+spec/encryption-with-barbican
Specifically, it outlines the use of Barbican as the key manager
for volume encryption.

A similar specification has been accepted by Nova -- see
http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/nova-specs/tree/specs/juno/encryption-with-barbican.rst
(or https://review.openstack.org/#/c/94918/ for the specification
review).

Co-authored by: Bruce Benjamin <bruce.benjamin@jhuapl.edu>

Implements: blueprint encryption-with-barbican
Change-Id: I0c40db39980d34dce34360474afb3e2bd45d8ad0

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-11 02:48:01.000000000', 'message': 'Add volume backup/restore functional test

Adds a more comprehensive test for the cinder volume resources:
- Creates a stack with a volume, and writes data to it
- Deletes the stack with the volume deletion policy set to
  "snapshot" (which really means backup) the volume
- Create a new stack with a volume created from the backup
- Prove the data written in the first stack is still present
Note this test also aims to provide coverage of volume attachment
resources, e.g so we would catch any bugs like bug #1311533 in
future.

Authored-By: Steve Hardy <shardy@redhat.com> based on tempest change
I04ae0cf942d12c4504b2df504a8c940575b90b69

Change-Id: I04ae0cf942d12c4504b2df504a8c940575b90b69
Related-Bug: #1311533
